<div id="accordion">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h5 class="mb-0">
        <button class="btn btn-link" id="<%= tool_name%>-help-heading" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#<%= tool_name %>-help" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="<%= tool_name %>-help">
          rip-git Help
        </button>
      </h5>
    </div>

    <div id="<%= tool_name %>-help" class="collapse" data-toggle="collapse" aria-labelledby="<%= tool_name %>-help-heading" data-parent="#accordion">
      <div class="card-body bg-light">
        <pre style="margin-bottom:0;">rip-git rips web accessible repositories, even when directory browsing is turned off.

When a service is found: rip-git -u %url% 
friendly name: git ripper
run in BG: true

Output files like gitrip-somefile.txt will be automatically parsed into the UI. Output file names generated from this page are automatically prepended with "gitrip-" and appended with ".txt"</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<div class="container no-gutters">
  <form id="<%= tool_name %>-options">
    <div class="row">
      <div class='col-sm-6'>    
        <%= erb :'tools/tool_helpers/_text_input', locals: {
                  tool_name: tool_name,
                  label: "Target",
                  field_name: "target",
                  field_value: "",
                  placeholder: "http://127.0.0.1/directory/.git"
                }
        %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
  <hr>
  <%= erb :'partials/_tool_runner', layout: false, locals: {tool_name: tool_name} %>
</div>

